put.mlc.classifiers.pcc.inference.montecarlo

Class FMeasureMaximizerInference

  • java.lang.Object
    • put.mlc.classifiers.pcc.inference.Inference
      • put.mlc.classifiers.pcc.inference.montecarlo.MonteCarloInference
        • put.mlc.classifiers.pcc.inference.montecarlo.FMeasureMaximizerInference
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, IInference

    public class FMeasureMaximizerInference
extends MonteCarloInference
    Implementation of General F-Measure Maximizer. This is one of inference methods of PCC algorithm. It is based on the Monte Carlo sampling.

    For more information, see:

    Krzysztof Dembczynski, Willem Waegeman, Weiwei Cheng, Eyke Hullermeier, "An exact algorithm for F-measure maximization", Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems 24 (NIPS-11): 223-230.
    Author:
    Krzysztof Dembczynski, Arkadiusz Jachnik, Adrian Jaroszewicz
    See Also:
